        "3"))
    return qs
}

// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  Section 7c. MMLU-Ko inline corpus (n=20, D4 drift fix)
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
//  Source authority: HAERAE-HUB/KMMLU / nayohan/mmlu-ko — Korean MMLU
//  translation. 4-option multiple choice across academic domains.
//  Inline sample = 20 items mixing humanities/STEM/social-science.
//
//  Same storage schema as hae_rae_items; answer_digit = "1".."4".

fn mk_item(qid: string, subject: string, prompt: string, answer: string) -> [string] {
    let mut r = []
    r = r.push(qid)
    r = r.push(subject)
    r = r.push(prompt)
    r = r.push(answer)
    return r
}

